---
name: dataset-groupBy
requires: Feature.Dataset
---

# Dataset — groupBy and reduceByKey

Word-count pattern: groupBy identity, then map to (word, count).
`reduceByKey` for incremental accumulation.

```scalascript
val words = Dataset.of("apple", "banana", "apple", "cherry", "banana", "apple")

// groupBy — each group is (key, List[items])
val grouped = words.groupBy(w => w).collect()
val sortedGroups = grouped.sortBy(_._1)
sortedGroups.foreach { case (word, occurrences) =>
  println(s"$word: ${occurrences.length}")
}

// reduceByKey — (word, count) pairs
val counted = Dataset.of(
  ("a", 1), ("b", 1), ("a", 1), ("c", 1), ("b", 1), ("a", 1)
).reduceByKey(_._1)((x, y) => (x._1, x._2 + y._2)).collect()
val sortedCounts = counted.sortBy(_._1)
sortedCounts.foreach { case (k, v) =>
  println(s"$k -> ${v._2}")
}
```
